# Endpoints & EndpointSlices

Service holds the **selector**. The **resolved Pod IPs** live in a separate object.

- **`Endpoints`** — original, one per Service, same name.
- **`EndpointSlice`** — modern (≥1.21), ≤100 per slice, low overhead at scale.

> Filled in by the **endpoints controller** when Pods go Ready / not-Ready / deleted. `kubectl get endpoints api` = the live answer.

## The #1 Services bug

> `endpoints: <none>` → **no ready Pod matches the selector.**

- selector ≠ Pod labels (typo)
- Pods not ready (probe / pulling)
- Pods in another namespace

`kubectl describe service <n>` — selector + addresses side by side.

## No-selector Service

> Hand-write `Endpoints` → a **Kubernetes name for an external IP** (RDS, legacy VM). Swap in-cluster later, clients unchanged.
